   <br>
    Was in LDoN this evening using both rapture and apathy side by side for overpulls since many tanks dont know what the word Lull means.Over the course of the 90 minutes we were inside not once was Apathy resisted,but then again the mobs we faced were somewhat lower in level than the mobs I faced a few days ago when making this post.<br>
<br>
    The mobs I faced a few days ago were in the mistmoore theme and at that time I was at lvl61 the lowest level in group.The remaining 5 members were all 65 thus the mobs tended to be Dark Blue or occasionally White to me when conned.<br>
<br>
    Today I was matched at 61st with 2 other toons of the same level and 3 remaining characters between 55 and 57 - all mobs in dungeon were D.Blue.Again like I said not once was Apathy resisted and I especially made sure to watch the workings of the spell this evening.Keeping Arcane Rune up helps considerably,and believe me in 90 minutes time testing different spells on varying mobs I recast AR at least 10 times.<br>
<br>
    Another word lost to many tanks is Taunt - after 10th level they forget how to do it.Believe it or not I was actually grouped in PoI a few levels ago with a Warrior that told me his Taunt skill was at 34.His excuse was that Warriors dont have the ability to peel mobs off of casters after level 50 so he didnt bother increasing skill.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
   One of the things I notice is that LDoN seems to be more of a special case than most other areas.Take a normal mission for your level and the mobs will have the same resists as mobs in any other area.Take a hard mission and the mobs themselves are not only slightly more difficult by having increased levels and hp,but also have higher resists,and many more that are totally immune to cetain effects.It is very possible the group of 65's I was with choose a hard mission thinking the levels would be thrown off in thier favor by taking someone lower in level then they were,perhaps thinking this would be to thier advantage.The Bard in group although lvl 65 was not able to charm mobs for instance,this fact was lost to me at the time and I didnt think about it.For a level 65 to have charm resisted by a mob that was charmable in a different group with different levels should have tipped me off to the problems I could face.<br>
<br>
   As for my ability to not have many mezz's resisted,this may also be due to the fact I try to have ALL stats buffed to max while on an adventure.Early on in my career I learned that charisma is supposed to effect roots and mezz's in addition to charms.My charisma is average 218 while in a group,in fact the only stat I allow to slip under 100 without thought is strength and that is at 84 unbuffed.Intell has been my prime concern and I have had that maxed at 255 for some time.<br>
